    <note>Shi(4) Gongru [21101] According to Zhu(1) Xi's [3257] funerary inscription for his grandson, Dun [20910] (q.v.), his ancestors were a distnguished lineage (youzu) of Xinchang and to avoid the Gengzi (1120) troubles (Rebellion of Fang(1) La [3298] ?), he moved to Linhai and was later granted an office by an edict of grace. His father did not hold office, but he was the great grandson of Daidan [13357]. CBD, 1, 421-2.</note>
